<subSubSection lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
(Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Distribution of Solanum interius Rydb." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.123.31738.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/305322" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">23</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rydb., Bull. Torrey Bot. Club 31: 641. 1905 [&quot;" authorityYear="1904" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum interius" order="Solanales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="interius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Solanum interius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to North America, and the most common species of morelloid in the Great Plains. It is less common west of the Rocky Mountains, and although it does extend to Arizona and western New Mexico, 
<taxonomicName family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. interius" order="Solanales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="interius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<pageBreakToken pageId="58" pageNumber="59" start="start">S</pageBreakToken>
. interius
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not occur on the Gulf Coast where it is replaced by 
<taxonomicName family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. nigrescens" order="Solanales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="nigrescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">S. nigrescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Records of 
<taxonomicName family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. interius" order="Solanales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="interius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">S. interius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for Canada (Saskatchewan, 
<bibRefCitation author="Harms, VL" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" refId="B103" refString="Harms, VL, 2006. Annotated catalogue of Saskatchewan vascular plants. Published by the author, Saskatoon." title="Annotated catalogue of Saskatchewan vascular plants. Published by the author, Saskatoon." year="2006">Harms 2006</bibRefCitation>
) have not been verified with voucher specimens, although it is to be expected there. Specimens annotated by Harms as 
<taxonomicName family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. interius" order="Solanales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="interius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">S. interius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in SASK are of 
<taxonomicName family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. emulans" order="Solanales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="emulans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">S. emulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Child s.n.</emphasis>
, collected 29 July 1941)
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="3240790" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.123.31738.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/305322" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" start="Figure 23" startId="F23">
